_sText:
de_bustpoo is a map that was made in the span of a weekend by me. don't let the stupid name and dev textures fool you, it's a serious map. and though it's probably not near perfect, I found it fun during the little testing I did. It supports long-range and close-range encounters, and there are lots of different positions that you can experiment with.

the map is split between two floor levels, with bombsite A and B placed on top of each other. CTs start fairly close to both bombsites, and can rotate between them easily. Ts have access to a garage door that opens up another route to bombsite B, a door that only terrorists can open when they are ready.

for my friend crack (sinful)

strafe map with a lil bit of technicality. 30-45s

wasn't able to do a lot of playtesting because I'm getting ready to leave for awhile and I wanted to get this out before then. there shouldn't be any map breaking skips or anything but it's always hard to tell lol. I ended up running out of time, so the polish isn't quite there (for example; the dustmotes on the 2nd stage are barely there) but I may come back to this idea/map later on next year and do something about it. I think I am quite burnt out at the moment from mapping, so we'll see.

THIS IS THE FINAL VERSION KEKW

We have addressed some of the complaints people had and fixed it.

The map has been made easier. It’s no longer tier 9, but more like 7.

 

-          Fixed ability to CP, triggers to function like in Kyoto. A lot more  CP friendly

-          Added a ladder at the end of stage 1 for Expert Zone, where ground boost doesn’t function properly.

-          Removed the 4th last stage ( x2 x2 x2 x2 to bhop )

-          Removed the long RB in the final stage.

-          Made the 3rd last valpect stage easier

-          2nd last stage start (layered surf) made easier

-          Final stage : Removed the booster bhops and x1 that follows after that, near the end in space. No more RNG involved and a lot easier. It’s now x1 straight to the end

_sText: Low effort map i made :)

hey guys. I genuinely believe that this map is the one that lifts me out of bhop mediocrity and into bhop averagility lol. I really enjoy this map though. I managed to get a lot of testing done from people and I am eternally grateful for them taking their time out to help me. Special thanks for lilac for uploading two different betas to his server (cutehops). Also huge thanks to Kris. he helped me so much with testing.

Map is either tier 3 or tier 4 I can't decide (leaning towards 4). The lowest segment I've seen so far so I'd say it's save to say the map is 1:40-1:50ish seconds. There are 7 stages, varying in length.

Originally for this map I had wanted it to be longer. However, I quite literally reached the brushside limit for this map and had to cut it short. Originally I had two bonuses and was planning for atleast 8 stages. Nonetheless, I don't think cutting the map short will take away from the quality at all. I hope everyone enjoys it! Thanks

Made this map over a couple of days, decided to upload it today.

IMPORTANT!
This map is supposed to be played 2v2, and supports nothing more!

de_wingman is a map desgined for 2v2 fights (like the wingman gamemode, get it?) featuring a single bombsite, a dust theme, and the layout of nuke's b site. It plays pretty similarly to how it would in CS:GO. Breakable windows, doors, and all. This map has a working navmesh with bot support.

In short, this map is a blend of Shortnuke from CS:GO and Dust. Also has some elements from CS:S Nuke.
